    PROCEDURE: 'HEAT cooker, add oil and brown chops on both sides. Remove chops. Add celery, green pepper, and onion; brown lightly. Add tomato, seasonings, bouillon cube dissolved in hot water, barbeque sauce, and molasses; mix well. Replace pork chops. CLOSE cover securely. Cook 12 minutes. Let pressure drop of its own accord. REMOVE chops from cooker. Thicken gravy with cornstarch mixed with water. Pour over chops. OPTIONAL: Substitute lean pork shoulder, cut in 1-inch cubes, for pork chops. ',
