    PROCEDURE: 'Heat Cooker, add oil and brown meat. Add onion, garlic, celery, and greenpepper. Saute lightly. Add tomatoes and liquid drained from beans and mushrooms, combine salt, pepper, chili powder, and wine. Mix well. Close Cooker securely. Cook 20 minutes. Cool Cooker at once. Add beans and mushrooms and reheat to boiling. Keep at low simmer for a few minutes for flavor development. Serve with warm garlic or corn bread.',
