    PROCEDURE: '1. Put 1 quart boiling water in a heavy 4 qt. saucepan. Combine corn meal, flour and salt;, stir into boiling water. 2. Slowly add cold water, stirring constantly to prevent lumps. 3. Cover and cook slowly 1 to 3 hours just so mixture glops slowly. either: 4. Serve hot with cherry pie filling or thickened sour cherries and milk. or: 4. Pour mush in bread pan(s). Next day, slice and fry in oil for breakfast. Serve with molasses, syrup, or jam/jelly. ',
