    PROCEDURE: 'For sauce, in a medium mixing bowl stir together the soup, milk, marjoram,and pepper. Set aside. In a 2-quart casserole layer half of each of the ham, onion, potatoes, and sauce. Repeat layers. Bake, covered, in a 350 F. oven about one hour or till the potatoes are nearly tender. In a small mixing bowl stir together the bread crumbs, parsley, and melted margarine. Sprinkle atop casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes more or till potatoes are tender. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. If desired, garnish with parsley sprig. ',
